HEADWORD: Sterno-
<hw>Ster"no-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A combining form used in anatomy to
indicate <xex>connection with</xex>, or <xex>relation to</xex>, <xex>the
sternum</xex>; <as>as, <ex>sterno</ex>costal,
<ex>sterno</ex>scapular</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sternocoracoid</ent>⟦br⟧
